cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and query applications. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with acoustic word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it uses side information in the form of known word pairs to train the neural network. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
